    "author_association": "MEMBER",
    "body": "Solidity is not the only language that does not have this property. Python for example, a language that is usually considered to be very intuitive or at least easy to learn behaves like that:\r\n\r\n```\r\n>>> a = [1,2,3]\r\n>>> b = [4,5]\r\n>>> ref = a\r\n>>> ref = b\r\n>>> a\r\n[1, 2, 3]\r\n>>> b\r\n[4, 5]\r\n```\r\n\r\n```\r\n>>> a = [1,2,3]\r\n>>> b = [4,5]\r\n>>> a = b\r\n>>> a\r\n[4, 5]\r\n>>> b\r\n[4, 5]\r\n\r\n```",
